        "description": "Generate a PDF invoice from selected line items of an estimate. The PDF is stored in S3 and the response includes a presigned URL for direct download. When `dueDate` or `reference` are provided they are printed on the generated PDF.\n\n**Path variable:**\n- `estimateId` (Long): The ID of the estimate\n\n**Required fields:**\n- `lineItemIds` (Array<Long>): IDs of the line items to include in the invoice. Must be non-empty and all must belong to the specified estimate.\n\n**Optional fields:**\n- `dueDate` (String, ISO date `YYYY-MM-DD`): Payment due date to display on the invoice. Omitting this field leaves `dueDate` as null.\n- `reference` (String, max 100 chars): Purchase order number or any other reference to display on the invoice. Omitting this field leaves `reference` as null.\n\n**Response:** Returns the created invoice record including `invoiceNumber`, computed totals, and a presigned S3 URL to download the generated PDF.\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST \"{{base_url}}/api/v1/estimates/1/invoice\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"lineItemIds\": [1, 2, 3],\n    \"dueDate\": \"2026-04-30\",\n    \"reference\": \"PO-2026-001\"\n  }'\n```"
      },
      "response": [
        {
          "name": "Generate Invoice - Success",
          "originalRequest": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"lineItemIds\": [1, 2, 3],\n    \"dueDate\": \"2026-04-30\",\n    \"reference\": \"PO-2026-001\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8080/api/v1/estimates/1/invoice",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "localhost"
              ],
              "port": "8080",
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "estimates",
                "1",
                "invoice"
              ]
            }
